MeshCore Finder

This project is a fork and substantial TypeScript rework of
kybl/meshcore-signal-tester by Aleš Janda:
https://github.com/kybl/meshcore-signal-tester

The upstream MIT licence and copyright notice are retained in LICENSE.
Ported concepts include the MeshCore companion BLE exchange, GPS kinematic
filter, spatial/indexing patterns, CSV handling, Web Audio cues, wake-lock
behaviour, and browser test patterns. Git history retains the original files.

Packet decoding uses @michaelhart/meshcore-decoder, version 0.3.x, distributed
under its own MIT licence:
https://www.npmjs.com/package/@michaelhart/meshcore-decoder

Bundled third-party components and their required copyright/licence notices are
listed in public/THIRD_PARTY_NOTICES.txt. That file is copied into every
production build.

Map tiles are requested from OpenStreetMap and attributed in the map UI.
